models/smol-holomyth-halloween-costumes-1e2305d63e084c1e966630496b6deb5b</a></li>\n<li>Modern people (kind of like doing their business on the street) stylized animated <a href=\"https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/populate-models-f93c7b439e6746f9a2d5963e628a5c4e#download\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/populate-models-f93c7b439e6746f9a2d5963e628a5c4e#download</a></li>\n</ol>\n<h2 id=\"3d-stylized-world\" style=\"position:relative;\">3D stylized world<a href=\"#3d-stylized-world\" aria-label=\"3d stylized world permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ol>\n<li>find out how to work with a height map. There is a book surface, I need collision shape over it. Basically, programmatically only, and it makes sense <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fEG_cnRQ1HI\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fEG_cnRQ1HI</a></li>\n<li>Grass <a href=\"https://stayathomedev.itch.io/stylized-grass-shader/download/eyJleHBpcmVzIjoxNzE5MTA0OTYwLCJpZCI6MjY3NjEzN30%3d%2eeeyYH0HeUmEFhALhivnqZ3dArGg%3d\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://stayathomedev.itch.io/stylized-grass-shader/download/eyJleHBpcmVzIjoxNzE5MTA0OTYwLCJpZCI6MjY3NjEzN30%3D.eeyYH0HeUmEFhALhivnqZ3dArGg%3D</a> and the video about it <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3ftcGTp-Se8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3ftcGTp-Se8</a></li>\n</ol>\n<h3 id=\"godot-addons\" style=\"position:relative;\">Godot addons<a href=\"#godot-addons\" aria-label=\"godot addons permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<ul>\n<li>Terrain 3d addon <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YtiAI2F6Xkk\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YtiAI2F6Xkk</a></li>\n<li>Grass as addon <a href=\"https://github.com/IcterusGames/SimpleGrassTextured\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/IcterusGames/SimpleGrassTextured</a></li>\n<li>Inventory system\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/expressobits/inventory-system/issues/35\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/expressobits/inventory-system/issues/35</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/alfredbaudisch/GodotDynamicInventorySystem\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/alfredbaudisch/GodotDynamicInventorySystem</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/peter-kish/gloot/tree/master\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/peter-kish/gloot/tree/master</a></li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n<li>Object random placing <a href=\"https://github.com/HungryProton/scatter\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/HungryProton/scatter</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://github.com/Maaack/Godot-Menus-Template\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Main menu template</a></li>\n</ul>\n<h3 id=\"sky\" style=\"position:relative;\">Sky<a href=\"#sky\" aria-label=\"sky permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h3>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p>Clouds: terrible tutorial <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sNXj0RN09ps\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sNXj0RN09ps</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Day-night change: interesting but doesn’t explain much, so bad tutorial <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_EeVDI-PVRw\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_EeVDI-PVRw</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Theory behind sky scattering and the shader example from NVIDIA <a href=\"https://developer.nvidia.com/gpugems/gpugems2/part-ii-shading-lighting-and-shadows/chapter-16-accurate-atmospheric-scattering\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://developer.nvidia.com/gpugems/gpugems2/part-ii-shading-lighting-and-shadows/chapter-16-accurate-atmospheric-scattering</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Water and water level <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7L6ZUYj1hs8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=7L6ZUYj1hs8</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>For fireflies - boid AI <a href=\"https://github.com/beneater/boids/blob/4c8ab4d98d382d68fbe03bb94fd51f981530fc65/boids.js\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://github.com/beneater/boids/blob/4c8ab4d98d382d68fbe03bb94fd51f981530fc65/boids.js</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Foliage shader for trees</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p>I tried to chill in the evening and just play with a foliage shader, somehow make low poly trees fluffy. I found none reference. I tried to adopt the first step from <a href=\"https://youtu.be/flbnFFZWcsc?si=4ROO-tM0OvfIWsag\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">a Unity tutorial</a>, something about vertex displacement or quad scattering. And, I am not sure how to scale the whole quad. I don’t know if I need to, maybe that can be achieved by other means, but that’s how I spent my evening</p>\n<p>But <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iASMFba7GeI\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this one</a> has better explanations</p>\n<h2 id=\"portals\" style=\"position:relative;\">Portals<a href=\"#portals\" aria-label=\"portals permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<p>In Godot 4.</p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ReMKWYmifN8\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">this</a> is what I need but it's Godot 3. So before we do that, look at the underlying implementation in <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cWpFZbjtSQg&#x26;t=0s\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">coding adventures</a>. This is a <a href=\"https://forum.godotengine.org/t/oblique-near-clipping-plane-for-camera/19388\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">question from Godot forum</a> that describes a port to Godot  And <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hchttF-iN7Y\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">more examples</a></li>\n<li>And <a href=\"https://www.terathon.com/lengyel/Lengyel-Oblique.pdf\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Oblique plane</a> <a href=\"https://github.com/godotengine/godot-proposals/issues/2713\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">proposed for Godot</a> (<a href=\"https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/89140\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">soon will be in version 4.4 or later</a>  or <a href=\"https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/85529\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">another approach</a> or <a href=\"https://github.com/godotengine/godot/pull/84454\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">another</a>). So, soon.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>And [this] is just a bonus.</p>\n<p>So, I chose the one from <a href=\"https://github.com/godotengine/godot/compare/master...V-Sekai:godot:override_projection_4.2\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Lyuma</a>. To carry it on you need to apply two commits</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">Commit 18e21e3\nLyuma &lt;xn.lyuma@gmail.com>\nPermit overriding the projection matrix passed to shaders without affecting culling logic.</code></pre></div>\n<p>and a fix for godot >= 4.3</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">Commit d7d6e385c271\nmajikayogames &lt;152851004+majikayogames@users.noreply.github.com>\nreverse z fix</code></pre></div>\n<p>So</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">scons -c\ngit checkout -b 4.4-beta-portals 4ce466d7fa7\ngit cherry-pick 18e21e3\ngit cherry-pick d7d6e385c271\nscons platform=windows</code></pre></div>\n<h2 id=\"pseudo-relief\" style=\"position:relative;\">Pseudo relief<a href=\"#pseudo-relief\" aria-label=\"pseudo relief permalink\" class=\"with-anchor after\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" height=\"20\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"20\">\n                <path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3\n                3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3\n                  9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64\n                  1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\">\n                </path>\n                </svg></a></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://3dmodels.org/blog/normal-maps-in-blender-guide/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://3dmodels.org/blog/normal-maps-in-blender-guide/</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://easy-peasy.ai/ai-image-generator/images/medieval-fantasy-cooper-coin-unique\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://easy-peasy.ai/ai-image-generator/images/medieval-fantasy-cooper-coin-unique</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.blender.org/manual/en/3.3/render/shader_nodes/vector/normal_map.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://docs.blender.org/manual/en/3.3/render/shader_nodes/vector/normal_map.html</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://docs.gimp.org/2.10/en/gimp-filter-normal-map.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://docs.gimp.org/2.10/en/gimp-filter-normal-map.html</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Lk1XlO_Df3M\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Lk1XlO_Df3M</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://3dmodels.org/blog/displacement-maps-in-blender-tutorial/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"external nofollow noopener noreferrer\">https://3dmodels.org/blog/displacement-maps-in-blender-tutorial/</a></li>\n</ul>","excerpt":"Resources low poly medieval scene in/on the book https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/medieval-fantasy-book-06d5a80a04fc4c5ab552759e9a97d91a Inn…","tableOfContents":"<ul>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#resources\">Resources</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#3d-stylized-world\">3D stylized world</a></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"#godot-addons\">Godot addons</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"#sky\">Sky</a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#portals\">Portals</a></p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><a href=\"#pseudo-relief\">Pseudo relief</a></p>\n</li>\n</ul>","fields":{"socialcard":"gatsby-plugin-social-card/edd7b53f-b7d1-5063-9850-ccca90e76845.jpg"},"frontmatter":{"date":"August 24, 2024","published":"August 24, 2024","lastModified":"August 24, 2024","title":"Life of NPC (working title)","subtitle":null,"section":null,"draft":null,"developing":null,"buttonText":null,"buttonLink":null,"secondButtonText":null,"secondButtonLink":null,"featuredImage":null}}},"pageContext":{"showLikes":true,"absolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikolasan.github.io/mikolasan.github.io/src/markdown/gamedev/life-of-npc.md","url":"/gamedev/life-of-npc","next":null,"previous":{"excerpt":"The basics will be based on First Person Shooter template. Some that I was considering: From chaffgames (docs) - weapon change animation…","fileAbsolutePath":"/home/runner/work/mikol